Class CalendarSyncRunnable

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Thread
      • com.mpagliaro98.mysubscriptions.model.CalendarSyncRunnable
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Runnable

    public class CalendarSyncRunnable
extends java.lang.Thread
    A thread class that runs the code to sync this app's model data with the calendar of the device this is running on.

        public CalendarSyncRunnable(android.content.Context context,
                            SharedViewModel model,
                            OnSyncCalendarListener caller)
        Create the thread class. This will save the application context and model so that they can be used while the thread is running.
        Parameters:
        context - the current application context
        model - the model containing all subscription data

    • Method Detail

      • run

        public void run()
        The code to run when the thread is running. This will delete the calendar if one was created during a previous sync, then create a new calendar, then add all of the events to it. Calendar API permissions must have been requested and accepted prior to this thread being run.
        Specified by:
        run in interface java.lang.Runnable
        Overrides:
        run in class java.lang.Thread

      • createSyncCalendar

        Parameters:

        name - the name of the calendar

      • deleteSyncCalendar

        private void deleteSyncCalendar(android.content.Context context)
        Delete the system calendar that was created by this app, if it exists. If it doesn't exist, this won't do anything.
        Parameters:
        context - the current application context

      • createSyncCalendarEvents

        private void createSyncCalendarEvents(android.content.Context context,
                                      int calID,
                                      Subscription subscription)
                               throws java.lang.SecurityException
        Add a set of events to the system calendar. This will loop through the next payment dates for the given subscription and add an event to the calendar for each one.
        Parameters:
        context - the current application context
        calID - the ID of the calendar the events will be added to
        subscription - the subscription to get next payment dates from
        Throws:
        java.lang.SecurityException - thrown if the app doesn't have permission to create events
